column95: [{"date":"2023-08-10T00:00:00.000Z","dateSeen":"2025-07-23T01:26:55.654Z","rating":5.0,"text":"I enjoyed living here. The apartments are architecturally pleasing with wide hallways, great views, and lots of light. The community is very well designed. The neighbors are nice. There is a nice pool, hot tub, BBQ, clubhouse, also well designed. My friends were always impressed when I brought them over. There is a nice bridge over a creek and wooded area which leads to a walkable shopping area with places to eat and coffee shops. Good school district. Great location. The property management team is professional and responsive. Jen and Tasha are especially standout property managers with a friendly professional attitude and excellent customer service. The management team was responsive and prompt when it came to maintenance. The only suggestions I have for improvement is the process for paying the last month's rent is needlessly confusing and a bit of a hassle. There were also two cars stolen in the year I was there, but these seem like isolated incidents, and the neighborhood itself and the surrounding is very safe, family oriented and upscale. I felt very safe there. Still, I think the apartment complex could be more vigilant about who they let come on the property. I see lots of friends of friends of friends using the pool and other facilities, and could consider beefing up security. Overall though, excellent experience. I would say Altitude is probably the best apartment complex in Kansas City.","sourceURLs":["https://www.apartments.com/altitude-970-kansas-city-mo/g65egbw/#yhzxwsv-2-unit"],"title":"A good place to live"},{"date":"2023-07-10T00:00:00.000Z","dateSeen":"2025-07-23T01:26:55.654Z","rating":5.0,"text":"Altitude 970 has been such an amazing home. From the amenities to the fixtures in the home I absolutely love it here. The office staff is so helpful and caring and maintenance makes sure to get things done quick. Definitely recommend!","sourceURLs":["https://www.apartments.com/altitude-970-kansas-city-mo/g65egbw/#yhzxwsv-2-unit"],"title":"LOVE THIS PLACE!"},{"date":"2021-11-16T00:00:00.000Z","dateSeen":"2025-07-23T01:26:55.655Z","rating":1.0,"text":"Management is just not what it’s used to and the lack of security is BEYOND frustrating. You will not feel safe at this property I can promise you that!","sourceURLs":["https://www.apartments.com/altitude-970-kansas-city-mo/g65egbw/#yhzxwsv-2-unit"],"title":"Just not worth the asking price"},{"date":"2021-08-03T00:00:00.000Z","dateSeen":"2025-07-23T01:26:55.656Z","rating":1.0,"text":"This place is visually amazing. However, don’t sign a contract here or you will be very disappointed. The turnover of staff including management is out of control. I have lived here just under 2 years and they have had 3 different property managers, 3 full maintenance staff changes, and a corporate team that is looking to cash in rather than making you feel welcome. Stay far away from this place. Check all reviews and do your research because we all have the same complaints.","sourceURLs":["https://www.apartments.com/altitude-970-kansas-city-mo/g65egbw/#yhzxwsv-2-unit"],"title":"Visual Fasad"},{"date":"2021-11-15T00:00:00.000Z","dateSeen":"2025-07-23T01:26:55.655Z","rating":1.0,"text":"Ever since being taken over by Sherman, this property has gone down hill. Utility cost are insane 300+ a month for electric. Constant crime issues lately and office staff refuse to care or do anything about it. I wouldn’t recommend anyone moving here","sourceURLs":["https://www.apartments.com/altitude-970-kansas-city-mo/g65egbw/#yhzxwsv-2-unit"],"title":"Horrible Management"},{"date":"2025-04-29T00:00:00.000Z","dateSeen":"2025-07-23T01:26:55.653Z","rating":1.0,"text":"I used to live in this apartment complex. Everything was great and well but the neighbors upstairs have such horrendous foot stomping that it echoes my whole living room and I lived on the 4th floor (5 floors max)","sourceURLs":["https://www.apartments.com/altitude-970-kansas-city-mo/g65egbw/#yhzxwsv-2-unit"],"title":"Thin Walls"},{"date":"2024-04-29T00:00:00.000Z","dateSeen":"2025-07-23T01:26:55.654Z","rating":1.0,"text":"Expect a long walk to your car every single time you want to use it. Unless you wanna pay hundreds of dollar for a private spot. They don’t have any public parking for guests since the parking is always full. I got a maintenance request and they locked the only door available to put my trash can in in my tiny tiny overpriced studio. Rent literally anywhere else.","sourceURLs":["https://www.apartments.com/altitude-970-kansas-city-mo/g65egbw/#yhzxwsv-2-unit"],"title":"Horrible"},{"date":"2022-03-05T00:00:00.000Z","dateSeen":"2025-07-23T01:26:55.655Z","rating":1.0,"text":"As I am writing this now there are police and FBI here, which doesn't surprise me since they are here every month it seems like. The complex is littered with dog poo because no one picks it up and management doesn't enforce it or have people take care of it. Our building specifically smells like cigarettes or weed even though there is a no smoking policy. They put notices on everyones door but the problem persists. Basically what you think your paying for here...luxury... it is far from it. The utilities are astronomical here and neither the complex nor the energy company knows why. I called both and neither whats to take responsibility. IN SHORT.. YOU CAN FIND A CHEAPER PLACE WITH THE SAME CRAP.","sourceURLs":["https://www.apartments.com/altitude-970-kansas-city-mo/g65egbw/#yhzxwsv-2-unit"],"title":"NOT Luxury Apartments"},{"date":"2021-07-09T00:00:00.000Z","dateSeen":"2025-07-23T01:26:55.656Z","rating":1.0,"text":"These apartments are beautiful. Granite counter tops, spacious floor plans, and wonderful amenities. Unfortunately that is where the buck stops. The walls are paper thin, and I paid higher utility bills here than I've ever paid anywhere else(even more than a house). The worst part of this property is its management-not necessarily the office staff. The corporate team that \\"oversees\\" this property are among the most two faced individuals you will ever encounter. They do not care about you or your situation, and when serious attention is needed, they will not give the property Manager or staff what is needed (materials, training, etc) to remedy the problem.","sourceURLs":["https://www.apartments.com/altitude-970-kansas-city-mo/g65egbw/#yhzxwsv-2-unit"],"title":"Deceptively beautiful apartments"}]

They charge you as far as they can!3)You will lose your mailing package if you live in Spectrum Apartments. There are a lot of mixed packages in three buildings. I experienced bad and impolite reactions from managers and staff several times. 5)Some nights, their workers forgot to take trash on time. The hallway was dirty most of the time.6)There always is a bad smelling in the hallway. 7)They show you a model unit that is totally different from the unit you are going to move in. They showed us a unit with new cabinets and kitchen stuff. However, when we moved in, we realized that all stuff is very old and different from what we saw in the model.8)When they are convincing you to rent their apartments, they are nice. However, when you move in, they will never respond to your emails and inquiries. column17: [{"dateSeen":"2025-02-10T20:25:00.000Z","value":"If you're looking for THAT home that needs nothing, then WELCOME HOME! Located in the active 55+ Highland Lakes community, here is a wonderful 2 bed/2 bath property with NEW roof, NEW vinyl plank flooring, NEW hurricane impact windows and front door, NEW exterior paint, newer A/C (2018), water heater (2017), electrical box and wiring (2018) and updated kitchen (2017) and bathrooms (2017)! Pride of ownership is apparent throughout and you will love the quiet tree lined cul-de-sac this property is on. The beautiful stone driveway and front path lead you up to the front door. As you step inside, you will be impressed by the space that this home offers. With ceiling fans in every room, there is ample room for entertaining or plenty of spots to just spread out and enjoy your home. The great room is very large and is home to both the dining room and living room while being open to the Florida room. The light and bright bonus Florida room is off the back of the house and overlooks the peaceful backyard where you can observe the birds and butterflies. The back door leads to the rear porch/lanai, which is surrounded by windows and offers access to the backyard. This room adds additional space for you to entertain or take in the lovely Florida weather. The kitchen boasts neutral color soft close cabinetry. The lower cabinets have pull out shelves, making storage so easy! There are beautiful quartz counters, garbage disposal, Stainless Steel appliances that include the 5 burner flat top stove, microwave, refrigerator and dishwasher, plus there is also a perfect spot for a table! The two bedrooms are generous in size. The hall bath is updated and has a lovely jetted tub, perfect for relaxing after a day at the beach. The primary bedroom has a wall closet in addition to a large walk-in closet and there is a beautifully updated ensuite bath with step in shower. The well kept garage has the washer and dryer, along with a large tub sink. The sprinkler system has a 100 foot well and zones 1 and 2 (of 3) have all been updated and have brand new heads. Imagine finding all of this in the wonderful Highland Lakes community that offers so much! There are three 9-hole executive golf courses, updated putting green and driving cages, shuffleboard, bocce ball, tennis/pickleball courts, Olympic sized swimming pool with spa, all types of activities including card room, billiards room, theater/auditorium, a lodge with fireplace and kitchen with scenic views overlooking the lake that has a heated swimming pool, patio with BBQ grills, horseshoe pits and so much more. Close to shopping, restaurants and beaches, this is the home you have been waiting for! Come and see today."},{"dateSeen":"2021-02-02T11:58:00.000Z","value":"Lovely maintained home with newer energy efficient windows, one year old stainless kitchen appliances with refrigerator with bottom freezer, A/C replaced in 2006, roof 2004, and exterior repainted with gutters and downspouts replaced. Enter home through beautiful mahogany front door with lovely etched glass insert. Enter into spacious foyer which leads to large great room and family room. Kitchen has eat-in area and pantry, window over sink and door to the garage. The back screened porch has a double-door for parking your golf cart and vinyl windows to keep the rain out and electrical outlets. Home is located on a cul-de-sac with lovely landscaping and limited traffic. The garage is actually a one and 1/2 car garage with lots of built-in storage (approx. 15x23) or 345 SF. This home is located in Highland Lakes, Pinellas County's premier 55+ community with 2 heated pools, 2 recreation buildings, an auditorium for dances, dinners and shows, 27-hole golf course with NO GREEN FEES, bocce ball, tennis, shuffleboard and pickleball courts. the Lodge sits on Lake Tarpon with fishing dock and home for 2 pontoon boats owned by the Association. Next to the Lodge is the RV and Boat storage lot for owners as space is available. The garage, screened porch and driveway have a special epoxy finish for easy maintenance and attractive appearance. Home has pest, lawn, gardening and security contracts."},{"dateSeen":"2021-08-20T14:17:00.000Z","value":"Welcome home to this lovingly cared for home with tons of updates for you to just move right in. 2 bedroom, 2 baths with a 1 car garage, this home features new vinyl plank flooring throughout majority of home, new hurricane impact windows and front door, updated kitchen with new cabinets, quartz counters and appliances, updated bathrooms as well with a jetted tub for relaxing, newer AC, and water heater. She was found professional, kind, courteous, and always honored her commitments.","sourceURLs":["https://www.apartments.com/la-reine-apartments-washington-dc/hz0t182/"]},{"date":"2017-10-27T00:52:18.127Z","dateSeen":"2025-07-05T21:38:00.000Z","sourceURLs":["https://www.forrent.com/dc/washington/la-reine-apartments/5z0t68p"],"title":"A great place to live!"},{"date":"2014-08-01T00:00:00.000Z","dateSeen":"2024-12-16T15:30:15.021Z","rating":5.0,"text":"I have lived at the La Reine apartments for a year now and have had a really pleasant experience. Below are a couple of topical reviews:Leasing/Office Staff:The two that work in the office have been some of the best and friendliest that I have ever dealt with in all of the apartments I've lived. First, I was in a hurry to sign a new lease when moving across the country and they rushed to get all of the paperwork and an apartment ready in two days. They are very courteous to notify everyone when there are issue (e.g. water to be turned off, etc.). They will also put in large packages into the apartment units if asked, which I think is beyond what many would do.Units:The units are really nice, especially now that most (all?) of them have hardwood floors (tile in the bath) and renovated kitchens with brand new appliances and counters/cabinets. (I'll plug my one real complaint here. The renovation of the kitchen left me kitchen-less for a few weeks, which was quite annoying.) I have an efficiency that is much larger than what I expected, so space (at least for me) is not an issue. The only minor issue I had with the unit was that the noise of others in the hall or people that close their unit doors too hard could leak into my unit. This actually has seemed to be diminished quite a bit when they installed carpet in the hallways - could be real or that I don't pay any attention. These noises are not too bad at all. I love my apartment overall.Common areas:Besides the mail room (which I think needs no review except that the lobby was renovated and looks newer/nicer), I have used only the laundry room and gym. The laundry room is pretty standard. Recently it has had some slight updates and new machines that don't solely require quarters, so that is nice. There is lots of machines (5-6 of each washers and dryers). There is also lots of room where some people hang their clothes to dry. The gym in the building is nice with a couple of treadmills, a bike, an elliptical and some free weights. It seems to be all newer equipment. There are also a couple of TVs for those that want to catch some shows while working out.Location:This apartment is sitting on Connecticut Ave. just below Chevy Chase Circle. There is a Safeway just two blocks up the road, which another couple of smaller stores (grocery, seafood, alcohol) within that range. There are also restaurants and other shops easily within a few minute walk (e.g. Starbucks, men's barber shop, dry cleaners). Walking a little south will put you in front of the Politics and Prose bookstore and another set of places to eat. There is a L2 bus line that stops right by the apartment that can take you into downtown DC or to the red line Van Ness metro stop. I think there is a bus line that goes to Friendship Heights as well. I walk to the FH station in about 10 minutes, so it's pretty close.Overall, this apartment is really nice. When looking for a home in the area (Chevy Chase DC), I found that the rents here were a little higher than other area buildings, but felt it was worth it for what I wanted. The building is from the 1920s and retains that charm inside and out. Great architecture, high ceilings, wood floors, glass door handles, French doors to the kitchen, etc. In addition to the charm, the building was redone not long ago, complete with new kitchens (solid surface counters, glass front cabinets, stainless appliances). The kitchens are very sweet and use space well. There is a small gym onsite (just a small fee to get the fob and then no charge) and the neighborhood is great for running if you prefer the outdoors. It's also close to a small commercial strip that is convenient: groceries, pharmacy, library, small historic movie theater, and a few restaurants. It is relatively quiet for DC, but I like that. Management was helpful during move-in and has been extremely responsive to maintenance requests (although there have been few). I have had NO pest issues, but keep my unit very clean. My unit is bright, breezy with the bay windows open, and sunny. The windows are newer and help with the street noise when closed. I haven't had significant issues with noise from other units, but may just have quiet neighbors. Generally, tenants seem to be the responsible and respectful type---I feel very safe and have had no issues. My only complaints come with an older building---heating system is old, cooling is through window units. The bathrooms are mostly original and could use updating (although clean, freshly painted when I moved in). With regard to location, Friendship Heights Metro is walkable (~.7 miles), but the roads to get there are dark/deserted at night, so I typically only walk to Metro during the day. There is a garage for a fee. I always find street parking, usually within a block or so, but sometimes I am 2 blocks away depending upon time of day. I renewed my lease and would recommend the building highly!! This is a great room concept home with 4 bedrooms or 3 bedrooms plus den, 3 bathrooms and split bedroom design. The great room features an abundance of natural light with large windows. The kitchen is a dream with gray cabinetry, stone countertops with waterfall at the island. Ideal gas cooktop with built in microwave and oven. The village is just a short distance from the Eryri National Park and the picturesque Nantlle Valley with direct access to the impressive south western slopes of Yr Wyddfa. On the edge of the village is a working vineyard which takes advantage of the southern facing hillsides and produces a fine sauvignon blanc. With the main shopping town of Caernarfon only 8 miles distant along with beautiful mountain and coastal scenery nearby, there is much to recommend."},{"dateSeen":"2025-07-23T07:54:00.000Z","value":"Enjoying a sunny southerly aspect with distant views over the surrounding countryside and hills is this spacious 3 Storey Mid Terrace House situated in a convenient central location within the village of Penygroes, being within easy walking distance of village amenities, schools and leisure facilities. The property offers 2 reception rooms on the ground floor with 3 bedrooms located on the first and second floors, the views improving all the more from the upper levels. In need of much modernising work, there is however much potential here to make this a fine spacious home. Externally, there's a lawned forecourt garden with privet hedging whilst to the rear is a further lawned garden with gated access to a service lane and dilapidated garage – removing the garage would provide useful off road parking for one vehicle. The property offers 2 reception rooms on the ground floor with 3 bedrooms located on the first and second floors, the views improving all the more from the upper levels. In need of much modernising work, there is however much potential here to make this a fine spacious home. Externally, there's a lawned forecourt garden with privet hedging whilst to the rear is a further lawned garden with gated access to a service lane and dilapidated garage – removing the garage would provide useful off road parking for one vehicle. Fitted with uPVC double glazing and benefiting from gas central heating, the accommodation briefly comprises: Entrance Hall, Lounge, Dining Room, Kitchen, Landing, 2 Bedrooms, Bathroom and 3rd Bedroom to second floor.//n//nPenygroes is positioned just off the main thoroughfare of the A487 linking the towns of Caernarfon and Porthmadog, making travel and commuting to work easy and convenient. The village is just a short distance from the Eryri National Park and the picturesque Nantlle Valley with direct access to the impressive south western slopes of Yr Wyddfa. On the edge of the village is a working vineyard which takes advantage of the southern facing hillsides and produces a fine sauvignon blanc. With the main shopping town of Caernarfon only 8 miles distant along with beautiful mountain and coastal scenery nearby, there is much to recommend.//n//n","This generous size 4 Bedroom Semi Detached Family Home has recently been beautifully renovated and offers a pleasant blend of modern and original features. Boasting an impressive Kitchen and a stylish Bathroom, it’s a house you will want to make your home.//n//nLocated close to the village centre and just a short walk to the schools and the leisure centre, “Isalun” is perfectly placed for all the family. This spacious and well appointed Semi Detached Home is tastefully decorated and briefly comprises of a welcoming Entrance Hallway that features a beautiful and original mosaic tile floor. The main Living area was once two rooms, but is now a spacious dual aspect room with a large Bay window and patio doors leading out to the rear garden. The Lounge has a laminated wood floor and also features a cast iron, multi-fuel stove that sits neatly upon a slate tiled hearth with a decorative wooden lintel above, and with ample room for a large family dining table, this really is the heart of the home. Beyond the Living area is a light and spacious Kitchen, fitted with a range of modern base and wall units, topped with a contrasting grey coloured work surface and is equipped with a gas hob and electric oven with an overhead extractor fan as well as a built-in microwave oven and an integrated dishwasher and a fridge/freezer. In addition, there is also a built-in speaker system so you can have music whilst you cook. Upstairs are 4 bedrooms, made up of a generous size Master Bedroom, 2 additional Double Bedrooms and a large Single Bedroom. All are served by a stylish part tiled ground floor Bathroom, fitted with a white bath suite, a vanity unit and an over bath shower. The property has a mains gas central heating system as well as uPVC double glazing throughout. So if you are looking for a more spacious family home, we highly recommend you book a viewing soon to get to the front of the queue.//n//n"]},{"key":"Brochure URL","value":["https://assets.reapit.net/dah/live/pdf.php?p=VAE230005&t=S"],"replace":"true"},{"key":"Key Features","value":["3 Storey Mid Terrace House","Modern Bathroom","Mains Gas Central Heating & uPVC Double Glazing","Convenient Central Village Location","Extensive Rear Garden","South Facing With Countryside Views","Potential Space For Off Road Parking","Requires Much Modernising Work","Gas Fired Central Heating","4 Good Size Bedrooms","Stylish Fully Fitted Kitchen","Generous Size Semi Detached Family home","Modernised & Well Maintained Interior","Valuable Off Road Parking","2 Reception Rooms & Kitchen","Lawned Gardens To Front & Rear","Modern Kitchen With Oven & Hob","Predominantly uPVC Double Glazed","Spacious Living Area","3 Bedrooms & Bathroom"]}]

Situated on a quiet tree-lined cul-de-sac, this spacious home offers a thoughtfully designed open floor plan with 4 bedrooms, 3 full baths, and a separate in-law suite.
